tafsir[2]{c,v,t}:
  49,12,"The main point of the call for Truth has always been that man should become a worshipper of God. He should associate with the one and only God his feelings of fear and love. But in every age it has happened that the contemporaries of the Prophet opined that his personality was too unimpressive to have been chosen by God as His messenger. Therefore, they refused to accept his words."
  49,16,"Here ‘inauspicious days’ means winter, for the Arabs called winter inauspicious."